The very first OREO cookie is produced in the Chelsea Market in Manhattan. Happy birthday to us!
OREO begins to teach people how to "twist, lick and dunk" together when the first advertisement showing the "twist" appears on trolley cars.
OREO goes global and begins exporting cookies to Central and Latin America.
OREO gets playful in the kitchen and introduces Double Stuf, giving eager fans twice as much of the "Stuf Inside".
Launch of "Father and Son" Moments campaign helps show the world how OREO can connect people, with a twist.
OREO gets into the spooky spirit and launches the Halloween OREO cookie with orange colored creme. Trick-or-treaters everywhere scoop them up, making it one of our most favorite limited editions.
Mini turns out mighty when OREO Mini takes cookie shelves and cookie jars by storm.
The votes are in, and we win! OREO cookies are now enjoyed by 9 out of 10 households. Guess no one was home in that tenth house.
OREO crosses mountains and reaches new heights to become China's #1 selling cookie.

When the lights go out during the NFL Championship Game, OREO lights up the internet with a single tweet. We get playful with the cultural moment and remind the world that they can still "Dunk in the dark".
If two times the creme isn't enough, how about triple? Minds are blown with the launch of OREO Mega Stuf.
We keep playing with our product and introduce fans to a thinner, crispier way to enjoy OREO with the launch of OREO Thins.
We play with tech and take to the skies to dunk in the biggest way yet, the OREO Drone Dunk.
Just when you think it can't get any better, we launch "Most Stuf". An OREO cookie with the most creme ever. Like, ever.

OREO cookies can be found in more than 100 countries! Making our mission to playfully connect people all over the world a reality. In fact, with over 40 billion cookies produced a year, when stacked, that's enough to circle the earth five times. So yeah, you could say that we get around.
For over 100 years, OREO has been bringing families together.

That's why we launched a partnership with PFLAG, the country's oldest LGBTQ+ ally organization, to create #ProudParent, a year- long initiative designed to shine a spotlight on the powerful impact love & acceptance can have on LGBTQ+ youth. Together we're committed to empowering and inspiring parents, families, and allies to come out in loud, public support.
